OL,3,CMinister who used parish as 'personal
OL,4,Cfiefdom' jailed
OL,6,FThe jury at Craigavon Crown Court also
OL,7,Ffound him guilty of defrauding a
OL,8,Fparishioner who has just lost her
OL,9,Fhusband of #1,000 between September 24
OL,10,Fand October 31, 2016
OL,12,FHis church has said a disciplinary
OL,13,Fprocess is underway.
OL,15,FMcLaughlin - who despite the jury's
OL,16,Fverdicts continues to maintain his
OL,17,Finnocence - was back in court on
OL,18,FTuesday were he was handed a 12-month
OL,19,Fsentence which was divided equally
OL,20,Fbetween prison and licence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/13
