OL,4,Cfiefdom' jailed
OL,6,FOver the period from August to
OL,7,FNovember 2016 the church didn't have a
OL,8,Ftreasurer and cheques issued from the
OL,9,Fchurch's accounts required two
OL,10,Fsignatures - one of which was
OL,11,FMcLaughlin's and the other from a
OL,12,Fnominated individual.
OL,14,FOn October 16, 2016 McLaughlin
OL,15,Fapproached the nominated individual
OL,16,Fand asked him to co-sign a cheque for
OL,17,F#10,000 which he said was to purchase
OL,18,Fa replacement organ.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/13
