OL,4,Cfiefdom' jailed
OL,6,FIn November 2016 a member of the
OL,7,Fcongregation took up the position of
OL,8,Ftreasurer.
OL,10,FWhen she examined the church's books,
OL,11,Fshe observed that the cheque stub for
OL,12,Fthe #10,000 transaction bore the name
OL,13,F'Northern Ireland Organs Limited'.
OL,15,FIt later emerged that McLaughlin had
OL,16,Finstead made the cheque out to himself.
OL,18,FRegarding the #1,000 fraud, Judge
OL,19,FLynch said this was handed to
OL,20,FMcLaughlin by a parishioner who had
OL,21,Fjust lost her husband.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/13
