OL,3,CMinister who used parish as 'personal
OL,4,Cfiefdom' jailed
OL,6,FFollowing what Judge Lynch described
OL,7,Fas an "acrimonious split" from his
OL,8,Fwife, McLaughlin is now the soul carer
OL,9,Fof their two teenage children.
OL,11,FDuring his trial, McLaughlin claimed
OL,12,Fthe allegations of fraud against him
OL,13,Fwere false and were mounted by his ex-
OL,14,Fwife and a 'cabal' of parishioners who
OL,15,Fhad taken her side when the marriage
OL,16,Fbroke down.
OL,18,FThese claims were rejected by the jury
OL,19,Fwho found him guilty on two charges of
OL,20,Ffraud by abuse of position in June.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/13
