OL,6,FAt sentencing, Judge Lynch spoke of
OL,7,F"the degree of trust" placed in
OL,8,FMcLaughlin in his position as a
OL,9,Fminister.
OL,11,FHe also spoke of the affect
OL,12,FMcLaughlin's offending had on the
OL,13,Fcongregation - and in particular the
OL,14,Fwidow he de-frauded and the nominated
OL,15,Findividual who co-signed the cheque
OL,16,Ffor #10,000.
OL,18,FJudge Lynch said he had read Victim
OL,19,FImpact Statements made by both
OL,20,Fparishioners.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/13
