OL,4,Cfiefdom' jailed
OL,6,FSaying McLaughlin was "in a position
OL,7,Fwhere a high degree of trust was
OL,8,Freposed in him", the Judge said he was
OL,9,F"cavalier with that trust" and that he
OL,10,F"almost regarded the parish as if it
OL,11,Fwas a personal fiefdom."
OL,13,FThe 12-month sentence was then imposed
OL,14,Fand as McLaughlin's two children sat
OL,15,Fin the public gallery, he was placed
OL,16,Fin handcuffs and was led into custody
OL,17,Fby prison staff. He will serve six
OL,18,Fmonths in jail and another six months
OL,19,Fon licence.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/13
